 SOCKET
--------
Socket is a communication mechanism that allow client/server to communicate with each other.
AF_UNIX to create socket for local communication.

There are various system call for this they are:-
socket()  	Create a socket for end-point communication.
bind()		To give the name to socket. so that other can identify it.
listen()	listen for connection on a socket.
accept()	To accept the connection from the client.
connect()	To connect to the server socket.
close()		To close the socket.

send() and receive() data on the socket. also read() and write() to communicate between server and client.

To compile the code:
gcc -o srvr srvr.c
gcc -o req_client req_client.c

Run:
./srvr 			in one terminal
./req_client		another terminal
